Seven people have been killed in a car crash on Umgeni Road in Durban this morning. eNCA's Dasen Thathiah is at the scene. Courtesy #DStv403 * Editor's note: The video above contains graphic visuals. Viewer discretion is advised. DURBAN - Mystery surrounds the tragic death of seven people killed in a car crash on Umgeni Road in Durban on Tuesday morning. Police officials are now suggesting that the vehicle may have been shot at. VIDEO: Seven people killed in KZN highway car crash The deceased and one survivor were trapped in the car, forcing officials to use the jaws of life. Captain Raj Rooplal of the Durban Accident Combating Unit said the car crashed into a barrier on the highway after the driver lost control of the vehicle. Captain Rooplal said bullet shrapnel and a bullet hole was found in the rear right end of the car.